   Canada's Trade Surplus
</HL>
<DATE>
07/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canada's merchandise trade surplus widened to
958 million Canadian dollars (US$826.9 million) in May,
partly because of an increase in motor-vehicle exports to the
U.S., Statistics Canada, a government agency, said.
   In April, the surplus totaled C$371 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Exports of trucks and other motor vehicles to the U.S.
rose by C$367 million in May. The U.S. took 74% of the total
May exports and supplied 70.5% of Canada's imports.
</TEXT>
