   Illinois Housing Development Authority -- $64.9 million of
residential mortgage revenue bonds through a Bear, Stearns &amp;
Co. group. The issue, which includes 1990 Series B, due Aug.
1, 1993-2000, 2010 and 2023, with capital appreciation bonds
due 2001-2006, and 1990 Series C, due Aug. 1, 1993-2000,
2010, and 2017, with capital appreciation bonds due
2001-2006, is priced to yield from 6.10% for Series C bonds
due in 1993 to 7.75% for Series B bonds due in 2023. Series B
consists of $45.9 million of bonds. Series B current interest
serial bonds are priced at par to yield from 6.30% in 1993 to
7.00% in 2000. There are $3.6 million of term bonds priced at
par to yield 7.13% in 2010 and $39.4 million of term bonds
priced at par to yield 7.75% in 2023. Capital appreciation
bonds are priced to yield to maturity from 7.20% in 2001 to
7.60% in 2005 to 2006. Series C consists of $19.2 million of
bonds. Series C current interest serial bonds are priced at
par to yield from 6.10% in 1993 to 6.80% in 2000. There are
$4.3 million of term bonds priced at par to yield 7.40% in
2010 and $11.6 million of term bonds priced at par to yield
7.50% in 2017. Capital appreciation bonds are priced to yield
to maturity from 7.05% in 2001 to 7.40% in 2005 and 2006.
Ratings of double-A by Moody's and single-A-plus by S&amp;P are
expected. Interest on the Series B bonds will be treated as a
preference item in calculating the federal alternative
minimum tax that may be imposed on certain investors.
   Philadelphia Regional Port Authority -- $56.1 million of
lease revenue bonds, Series 1990, due Aug. 1, 1991-2005, 2010
