                       ASSET-BACKED
                                                                                                       

   Fleetwood Credit Corp. -- $122 million of securities
backed by recreational vehicle loans are being offered with a
coupon rate of 9% at 99 18/32 to yield 9.204% through First
Boston Corp. The offering, FCC 1990 -- a Grantor Trust, was
priced at a yield spread of 0.94 percentage point above the
interpolated three-year and four-year Treasury notes.
Underlying loans are being serviced by Fleetwood Credit, a
unit of Fleetwood Enterprises. Legal final maturity is July
15, 1997. The issue has an expected average life of 3.4 years
assuming monthly prepayments at 1% of the original loan
balance. The offering is expected to be rated triple-A by
Moody's and S&amp;P, based on the quality of the underlying loans
and a surety bond from Capital Markets Assurance Corp., a
unit of Citicorp.
                                                                                                       

