<LP>
   PENNSAUKEN, N.J. -- Environmental Control Group Inc. said
its president and chief executive officer, Brian Esher, 42
years old, assumed the additional duties of chairman,
succeeding John Stoddard, who left the company for "personal
reasons."
   Mr. Stoddard had held the position of chairman since early
1989; he relinquished duties as chief executive to Mr. Esher
in September.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The asbestos abatement and insurance company also reported
net income of $481,000, or seven cents a share, compared with
year-earlier net of $971,000, or 14 cents a share; revenue
fell to $14.7 million from $17.2 million.
   The company also said it has relocated its headquarters
from Maple Shade, N.J., to an existing facility in
Pennsauken.
