   Business Brief -- American Capital Management:
   Primerica Agrees to Acquire
   Rest of Shares in Company
</HL>
<DATE>
07/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   PA ACA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Primerica Corp., New York, definitively agreed to acquire
the 17.4% of American Capital Management &amp; Research Inc. it
doesn't already own for stock or cash, at shareholders'
option.
   Primerica, a financial-services company, will pay either
0.32 share of its stock or $11.50 cash for each of the more
than 4.2 million American Capital shares it doesn't already
hold.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   American Capital, Houston, provides investment advice to
mutual funds and investment firms. The transaction was
announced in May; the companies expect to close the purchase
in late September or early October.
   Separately, American Capital reported that second-quarter
net income was flat at $5 million, or 21 cents a share, as
revenue eased 4.8% to $24.5 million.
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Primerica shares fell 50 cents to $36.875 while American
Capital's shares were unchanged at $11.50.
