   Business Brief -- Metropolitan Circuits Inc.:
   Stake Is Set for Consultants
   If They Raise New Capital
</HL>
<DATE>
07/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MPB
</CO>
<LP>
   Metropolitan Circuits Inc. said it would sell options to
buy as much as a 37.5% interest in the circuit-board maker to
two consultants if they are successful in raising new capital
for the cash-starved concern.
   Kenneth C. Cleveland and Paul G. McNamara also would
become the Santa Ana, Calif., company's top executives if
they raise "in the range of $2 million to $3.5 million"
within 30 days, said Richard J. Sandberg, chairman, president
and chief executive officer.
</LP>
