   Mr. Sandberg said the funds would be used for working
capital and to pay about $1.5 million in overdue debts to
suppliers. The company has no bank debt, he said.
   Mr. Cleveland, a crisis-management consultant, would
become chairman and chief executive officer, and Mr.
McNamara, former president of Aeroscientific, an Anaheim,
Calif., circuit-board maker, would be named president and
chief operating officer, if they obtain the financing. Mr.
Sandberg would relinquish those titles and become vice
chairman.
